# Every AIB in //bundles/assembly/BUILD.gn has a same-named group in this file,
# which is the list of all inputs that make up that AIB, which need to come from
# GN instead of being created within Bazel itself.
#
# For every GN-produced bazel input, there is a directory below this one which
# has the same path as that input has in GN. ie //src/lib/foo:bar will be a
# target named 'bar' in
# '//bundles/assembly/bazel_inputs/src/lib/foo/BUILD.gn'
#
# Currently, this only contains:
#  - packages (of any package set)
#
# Other inputs will be added in successive CLs.
#
# The idea is that eventually, all of those inputs will be created within Bazel
# itself, and then
# this GN file, and those in the subdirectories below this one, will all be
# deleted.

